# Integration Test Conventions

## Every new test fixture

- Inherit from `IntegrationTestBase` (provides `Factory`, `NewUser()`, and `[OneTimeSetUp/TearDown]`)
- Place in `Tests/<FeatureArea>/` mirroring the request folder structure (`Tests/League/`, `Tests/LeagueManager/`, `Tests/Royale/`, etc.)
- One `[TestFixture]` class per feature area

## Test data

- Always use `NewUser()` for user credentials — never hardcode emails or display names
- Build state through the API; never insert directly into the DB

## Typed contracts

- `PostJsonAsync<TRequest>` and `PostJsonAndDeserializeAsync<TRequest, TResponse>`: always pass a concrete request type from `FantasyCritic.Web.Models.Requests.*`
- `GetAndDeserializeAsync<TResponse>`: always pass a concrete ViewModel from `FantasyCritic.Lib.SharedSerialization.API.*`
- Never use anonymous objects or `JObject` — compile-time breakage on contract changes is the goal

## Running

- Run with `-c Release` when the dev web server is running (dev server holds Debug DLL locks)
- MySQL Docker container must be up first: `docker compose -f infrastructure/docker-compose-mysql.yaml up -d`

## No cleanup

Tests use GUID-based unique identifiers; they never collide across runs and require no teardown.
